HOST: https://api.utopian.io/api

# Utopian

The web API that powers https://utopian.io, the project that rewards hard working
open source contributors. Data is split between the STEEM blockchain and the API
server to ensure a reliable and stable platform for all of its users. A centralized
API allows a separate permissions model to be embedded within the server to overcome
any limitations the blockchain has to achieve Utopian's goal. Funds are effectively
paid through the STEEM blockchain.

## Authentication [/]

For external apps that want to enable Utopian posting, the author of that post
must exist on the Utopian platform. This is to ensure the moderation cannot be
hindered. External apps can use https://utopian.io/connect for the `redirect_uri`
and specify their own redirection endpoint to the `state` when authenticating with
SteemConnect2.

Example:

`https://v2.steemconnect.com/oauth2/authorize?client_id=utopian.app&response_type=code&redirect_uri=https://utopian.io/connect&state=https://google.com&scope=vote,comment,comment_delete,comment_options,custom_json,claim_reward_balance,offline`
This will redirect the user to [Google](https://google.com). However for security,
the `session` ID will not be released to the redirection callback.

### Login [POST /login]

Logs in the user using SteemConnect2 after they confirmed they want to login using
the OAuth workflow. This is required for full interaction with the STEEM blockchain.
If the user does not exist, they will automatically be created.

The following are the required scopes for a successful authentication:
- vote
- comment
- comment\_delete
- comment\_options
- custom\_json
- claim\_reward\_balance
- offline

+ Request (application/json)
    + Attributes
        + code (string, required) - OAuth code.

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        {
            "session": "secret-session-id",
            "expiry": 1516139588,
            "user": "elear"
        }

### Logout [POST /logout]

Destroys the session, rendering it unusable with endpoints that require an
authenticated user.

+ Request

    + Headers

            session: secret-session

+ Response 200 (plain/text)

