### Set Ban Status [POST /users/{user}/ban]

+ Parameters
    + user (string, required)

+ Request (application/json)

    + Headers

            session: secret-session

    + Attributes
        + banned (enum[number], required) - Ban status.
            Setting this to `0` will effectively remove any ban status from the
            user, regardless of the `bannedUntil` parameter.
            + Members
                + `0`
                + `1`
        + bannedBy (string, required) - Moderator who banned or unbanned the user.
        + banReason (string, required) - Reason of the ban.
        + bannedUntil (string, required) - ISO date string when the ban expires.

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        {
            "account": "elear",
            "banReason": "elear can't be banned :)",
            "bannedBy": "<utopian-system>",
            "bannedUntil": "1970-01-01T00:00:00.000Z",
